Package: StatVizR
Type: Package
Title: Statistical Analysis and Visualization Tools in R
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2024-04-26
Author: Nicolas Pedraza
Maintainer: Nicolas Pedraza <nicolas32@usf.com>
License: CC0
Description: StatVizR is an R package designed to streamline statistical analysis and visualization tasks.
It provides a comprehensive set of functions to facilitate data manipulation, exploratory data analysis (EDA), hypothesis testing, regression analysis, and plotting. 
Whether you're a beginner or an experienced data analyst, StatVizR aims to enhance your data analysis capabilities and streamline your workflow. T
he package includes functions for computing descriptive statistics, creating various types of plots (e.g., histograms, scatter plots), performing hypothesis tests, and conducting linear regression analysis.
With StatVizR, you can efficiently analyze your data and visualize your findings, enabling you to make informed decisions based on your data.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
